<figure><img src="https://farm4.staticflickr.com/3916/14474707953_75370ec616_c.jpg" alt="Destroyed Motorcycle Sprocket"><figcaption>It wasn't looking good before, but between Copiapo and Santiago it got a lot worse. It's starting to resemble a ninja star, and it was making a horrible noise any time I tried to roll the motorcycle backwards. </figcaption></figure><figure><img src="https://farm3.staticflickr.com/2927/14453188452_c213650bbf_c.jpg" alt="Dead Chain"><figcaption>The first thing I noticed was that the rollers were missing. Of course, that's happened to me before. As much as I hated it, I made the choice to try to make it to Santiago (which is my it's my own dumb fault my chain broke). But, the thing I've never seen before is that the teeth ate away the inside sleeve and started to dig into the master link.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="https://farm6.staticflickr.com/5504/14431436206_93ce7eb563_c.jpg" alt="Walking"><figcaption>Went on a walk with Jane and friends. </figcaption></figure><figure><img src="https://farm4.staticflickr.com/3847/14453193142_801f3e31f2_c.jpg" alt="Santiago"><figcaption>Walking Around Santiago</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="https://farm4.staticflickr.com/3926/14453436264_87b855e00a_c.jpg" alt="Santiago Canal"><figcaption>A lot of Santiago runs along this &quot;river&quot;. The river itself isn't particularly pretty, but there are some nice parks all along it.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="https://farm6.staticflickr.com/5193/14267912409_29838d2e76_c.jpg" alt="Locks on a Bridge"><figcaption>A good place to go with a lover, or for lock picking practice.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="https://farm3.staticflickr.com/2938/14268108497_8a4db9dfb4_c.jpg" alt="Nacho"><figcaption>The only photo I got of Nacho on our night out was at the very last instant. A mistake. </figcaption></figure>